# LeetCode 1 â€“ Two Sum (Java)

## ğŸ“Œ Problem Description
Given an array of integers `nums` and an integer `target`, return the indices of the two numbers such that they add up to `target`.

You may assume that each input has exactly one solution, and you may not use the same element twice.

---

## ğŸ’¡ Approach Used (Brute Force)
- Iterate through the array using two nested loops.
- Check every possible pair of elements.
- Return the indices immediately when the sum equals the target.

This approach is simple and easy to understand, making it suitable for beginners.

---

## ğŸ§  Algorithm
1. Loop from index `0` to `n-2`.
2. For each index `i`, loop from `i+1` to `n-1`.
3. If `nums[i] + nums[j] == target`, return `{i, j}`.
4. Return an empty array if no solution is found.

---

## âš™ï¸ Complexity Analysis
- **Time Complexity:** `O(nÂ²)`
- **Space Complexity:** `O(1)`

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Implementation (Java)

```java
class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target) {
        int n = nums.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if (nums[i] + nums[j] == target) {
                    return new int[]{i, j};
                }
            }
        }
        return new int[]{}; // if no solution found
    }
}
